# Magic Context → AstrBot Port — Gap Review v2

## Architecture Decisions (from AstrBot analysis)

These decisions eliminate entire TS source files from porting scope:

| Decision | TS files skipped | Reason |
|----------|-----------------|--------|
| `@filter.on_agent_begin()` exposes per-part `ContentPart` + `tool_call_id` | `tag-part-guards.ts`, `apply-operations.ts`, `tool-drop-target.ts` | AstrBot's message model is `list[ContentPart]` natively; no need for §N§ prefix parsing or composite `ownerMsgId\x00callId` keys |
| `tool_call_id` is globally unique in AstrBot | `tool-index.ts`, FIFO owner pairing | No need for composite-key tag index or legacy NULL-owner adoption |
| Messages flow to LLM providers → §N§ tags in message content would leak | `tag-messages.ts` §N§ prefix injection | Tags stored in DB only, matched by `message_id`/`tool_call_id` |
| `TextPart.mark_as_temp()` for transient content | `system-injection-stripper.ts` injection detection | AstrBot has native temp content API |
| Phase 7 (memory) skipped per user directive | All `ctx_memory`/embedding/FTS5/notes tables and modules | Other AstrBot plugins provide long-term memory |
| No OpenCode dashboard integration | `compartment-runner-state-file.ts`, dreamer subagent | AstrBot has no equivalent dreamer/scheduler infrastructure |

## Corrected Scope: What Actually Needs Porting

### Module: storage (`storage-db.ts`, `storage-tags.ts`, `storage-ops.ts`, `compartment-storage.ts`)

**Skip**: `storage-source.ts`, `storage-notes.ts`, `storage-meta-shared.ts`, `storage-meta-persisted.ts`, `storage-meta-session.ts`, `compression-depth-storage.ts`, `message-index.ts`, `memory-*.ts`, `dream-*.ts`, `project-key-*.ts`

**Keep**: 
- [x] Core CRUD: assign_tag, get_active_tags, get_tags_by_session, get_max_tag_number, update_tag_status, update_tag_drop_mode, update_tag_byte_size, update_tag_message_id, update_caveman_depth, delete_tags_by_message_id, clear_session_tags
- [x] Pending ops: queue_pending_op, get_pending_ops, clear_pending_ops
- [x] Compartments: save_compartments, get_compartments, append_compartments, get_last_compartment_end_message
- [x] Session facts: replace_session_facts, get_session_facts
- [x] Session meta (core): get_or_create_session_meta, update_session_meta

**Still missing from keep-list**:
- [ ] `get_tag_number_by_message_id` — needed for recovery/resume
- [ ] `get_tag_by_id` — needed for single-tag lookup during drop confirmation
- [ ] `update_tag_input_byte_size` — needed for tool-call size tracking via tc.id
- [ ] `removePendingOp` — needed for selective op retraction after cancel

### Module: caveman (`caveman.ts`, `caveman-cleanup.ts`)

**Skip**: Nothing significant — caveman is deterministic text compression, fully AstrBot-agnostic.

**Keep**: 
- [x] protect_regions, restore_regions, caveman_compress (lite/full/ultra)
- [x] caveman_level_for_depth, compute_target_depth
- [x] apply_caveman_cleanup, replay_caveman_compression

**Still missing**:
- [ ] `get_source_contents` batch — caveman currently compresses from `target.get_content()` which may already be compressed; original needs per-tag pristine-origin fetch from a `source_contents` table (or we store original text in the tags row itself as an `original_text` extra column)
- [ ] Caveman depth NOT persisted to DB after `apply_caveman_cleanup` — needs `update_caveman_depth` call per compressed tag
- [ ] `replay_caveman_compression` lacks session_id/db params — cannot re-apply persisted depths on restart

### Module: strip (`strip-content.ts`)

**Skip**: `strip-system-injected-messages` (AstrBot has `TextPart.mark_as_temp()`), `strip-dropped-placeholder-messages` (placesholders are AstrBot-specific not DB-encoded), `strip-processed-images` (AstrBot image model differs)

**Keep**:
- [x] strip_thinking_tags, strip_inline_thinking
- [x] strip_cleared_reasoning, clear_old_reasoning

**Still missing**:
- [ ] `replay_cleared_reasoning` — missing `persisted_watermark` gate; strips ALL messages unconditionally instead of watermark-gated
- [ ] `replay_stripped_inline_thinking` — same watermark-gate problem
- [ ] `truncate_errored_tools` — missing watermark parameter; processes ALL tools unconditionally

### Module: historian (`compartment-runner-*.ts`, `compartment-prompt.ts`, `compartment-parser.ts`, `read-session-chunk.ts`)

**Skip**: `compartment-runner-compressor.ts` (entire LLM-based re-compression pass — deferred to later phase), `compartment-runner-drop-queue.ts` (drop queueing tied to OpenCode message mutation model)

**Keep**:
- [x] COMPARTMENT_AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT, HISTORIAN_EDITOR_SYSTEM_PROMPT
- [x] build_historian_editor_prompt
- [x] parse_compartment_output (XML parsing)
- [x] build_existing_state_xml
- [x] Basic 9-step pipeline skeleton (validate → offset → state XML → format → LLM → parse → store)

**Still missing (keep-list)**:
- [ ] `run_validated_historian_pass` — retry loop (MAX_HISTORIAN_RETRIES=2 with exponential backoff)
- [ ] `build_historian_repair_prompt` + repair retry path
- [ ] `run_fallback_historian_pass` — fallback model retry
- [ ] `validate_historian_output` — structured validation (gap healing, coverage check)
- [ ] `validate_chunk_coverage` — chunk ordinal coverage validation
- [ ] `is_transient_historian_prompt_error` — retry classification
- [ ] `get_protected_tail_start` — hasMeaningfulUserText filtering (counts only meaningful user turns, skips pure notifications)
- [ ] `read_session_chunk` — token-budgeted chunking with block-merging and tool-only range tracking
- [ ] `map_parsed_compartments_to_chunk` — chunk-line ordinal → messageId resolution
- [ ] `queue_drops_for_compartmentalized_messages` — tag-based drop queueing (skipped per decision, but need equivalent using AstrBot's tool_call_id instead of composite keys)
- [ ] `promote_session_facts_to_memory` — skipped (Phase 7)

### Module: orchestration (`transform.ts`, `transform-postprocess-phase.ts`)

**Skip**: `create_transform` scheduler logic (AstrBot's hook system provides execution timing via filter priorities; no need for context-usage-based defer/execute decisions), `clear_message_tokens_cache`, `create_nudge_placement_store`, `run_post_transform_phase` (1006 lines — most subcomponents are OpenCode-specific: nudge injection, todo synthesis, auto-search hint, deferred marker drain, emergency bypass)

**Keep**:
- [x] Linear 6-phase pipeline via AstrBot hooks (on_agent_begin ×3, on_llm_request ×2, on_llm_response + after_message_sent)

**Still missing from keep-list**:
- [ ] Postprocess: pending-op materialization gating (decide whether to materialize queued drops now or defer)
- [ ] Postprocess: sentinel replay/persistence (re-apply droppped/truncated statuses from DB into active messages)

